    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sarah_gavron_748522",
        "quote": "It's interesting when you read the debates in parliaments between MPs about whether they should give women a vote. It's a lot of fear; it is fear of change. It's fear if women get to vote, family structures will break down. Women will stop having children. Women won't vote for war.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sarah Gavron",
            "url": "/quotes/sarah_gavron_748522"
        },
        "topics": [
